United States Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. Submitted Aug. 14, 2003. Decided Aug. 20, 2003. Glendora, Appellant Pro Se. Before WILLIAMS, KING, and GREGORY, Circuit Judges.

Affirmed by unpublished PER CURIAM opinion.

PER CURIAM.

Glendora appeals the district court’s order denying relief on her civil rights complaint. We have reviewed the record and find no reversible error. Accordingly, we affirm for the reasons stated by the district court. See Glendora v. Jacobs, No. CA-03-1166-MJG (D.Md. Apr. 30, 2003). We dispense with oral argument because the facts and legal contentions are adequately presented in the materials before the court and argument would not aid the decisional process.

AFFIRMED.
